main.command.parser

Class DateTimeParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.command.parser.DateTimeParser

  • public class DateTimeParser
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class for parsing dates and times from strings, uses DateParser and TimeParser for the actual date and time parsing.

      • parseDateTimesInSequence

        public static DateTimePair parseDateTimesInSequence(java.lang.String dateTimeString)
        Parses dates and times from args into a DateTimePair. This method parses the dates and times in sequence, so "5 Nov to 6 Nov 3pm" will be parsed with 3pm in the second time instead of the first.
        Parameters:
        dateTimeString - the string possibly containing dates and times
        Returns:
        a DateTimePair representing the dates and times found

      • parseDateTimes

        public static DateTimePair parseDateTimes(java.lang.String dateTimeString)
        Parses dates and times from args into a DateTimePair. This method does not parses the dates and times in sequence, so "5 Nov to 6 Nov 3pm" will be parsed with 3pm in the first time instead of the second.
        Parameters:
        dateTimeString - the string possibly containing dates and times
        Returns:
        a DateTimePair representing the dates and times found
